==English==
===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|detonare|detonāre|lang=la}}. It meant "to stop thundering", e.g. as in weather (''de-'' = "from", ''tonare'' = "to thunder"). The current English meaning seems to be a new formation in postclassical times.

===Pronunciation===
det"o*nate

===Verb===
{{en-verb|detonat|ing}}

# {{intransitive}}: To [[explode]]; to blow up. Specifically, to [[combust]] [[supersonic]]ally via [[shock]] [[compression]].
# {{transitive}}: To cause an [[explosion]].

